2026-04-11 14:43:21,253  INFO      mcp.server -- MCP execute_tool: execute_script  inputs={'script': 'import math\n\n# Conversion utility (10mm = 1.0 cm)\nside_length_cm = 1.0\n\n# For a regular hexagon, the circumradius (R) equals the side length (s).\nR = side_length_cm\n\n# 1. Create the sketch on the XY plane\nsketch_name = "Hexagon_Sketch_10mm"\ntry:\n    sketch = rootComp.sketches.add(rootComp.xYConstructionPlane)\n    sketch.name = sketch_name\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f"Error creating sketch: {e}")\n    raise\n\n# 2. Define the 6 vertices (using angles 0 to 5 * 60 degrees)\nvertices = []\nfor i in range(6):\n    angle_degrees = i * (360.0 / 6.0)\n    angle_radians = math.radians(angle_degrees)\n    x = R * math.cos(angle_radians)\n    y = R * math.sin(angle_radians)\n    vertices.append(Point3D.create(x, y, 0))\n\n# 3. Draw the lines connecting the calculated vertices\nlines = sketch.sketchCurves.sketchLines\nfor i in range(6):\n    p_start = vertices[i]\n    p_end = vertices[(i + 1) % 6] # Connect last point back to first point\n    lines.addByTwoPoints(p_start, p_end)\n\nprint(f"Successfully sketched a hexagon with {side_length_cm} cm sides named \'{sketch_name}\' on the XY plane.")'}
